'''Karen Cho''' is a Chinese-Canadian documentary filmmaker in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], Canada. Her credits include the 2004 [[National Film Board of Canada]] (NFB) documentary ''In The Shadow Of Gold Mountain'', documenting the effects of the [[Chinese Immigration Act, 1923|Chinese Exclusion Act in Canada]];<ref name="Keung">{{cite news | url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/731626681.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Nov+06%2C+2004&author=Nicholas+Keung&pub=Toronto+Star&desc=Documenting+Canada's+head-tax+history%3B+Immigrants+from+China+recall+woes+for+Karen+Cho+Film+won't+let+us+Canadians+forget+'skeletons+in+closet'&pqatl=google | title=Documenting Canada's head-tax history; Immigrants from China recall woes for Karen Cho Film won't let us Canadians forget 'skeletons in closet' | work=[[Toronto Star]] | date=November 6, 2004 | accessdate=February 5, 2013 | author=Keung, Nicholas | format=abstract}}</ref><ref name="Shadow">{{cite video | url=http://www.nfb.ca/film/in_the_shadow_of_gold_mountain/ | title=In the Shadow of Gold Mountain | publisher=National Film Board of Canada | date=2004 | people=Karen Cho, writer/director | medium=Documentary film}}</ref> the 2009 [[InformAction]] documentary ''Seeking Refuge''; and the 2012 NFB documentary ''[[Status Quo? The Unfinished Business of Feminism in Canada]]'', which was named best documentary at the [[Whistler Film Festival]].<ref name="Takeuchi">{{cite news | url=https://www.straight.com/blogra/whistler-film-festival-2012-director-karen-cho-status-quo-feminism-canada | title=Whistler Film Festival 2012: Director Karen Cho on the Status Quo of feminism in Canada | work=[[Georgia Straight]] | date=December 3, 2012 | accessdate=February 5, 2013 | author=Takeuchi, Craig | location=Vancouver}}</ref>
After graduating from the [[Mel Hoppenheim School of Cinema]], Cho made ''In The Shadow Of Gold Mountain'' at the NFB via a program for emerging filmmakers of colour.<ref name="CTV">{{cite news | url=http://montreal.ctvnews.ca/newsmaker-ravida-din-and-karen-cho-on-nfb-funding-cuts-1.795344#ixzz2K5CayCuc | title=Newsmaker: Ravida Din and Karen Cho on NFB funding cuts| work=[[CTV News]] | date=April 12, 2012 | accessdate=February 5, 2013}}</ref>
